# Issue Workflow

| Condition | Workflow |
|-----------|----------|
| `Modules` overlaps any other **ready** issue (`Unblocked` or `Isolate`) | **Isolate** — one issue at a time |
| `Unblocked` and disjoint `Modules` from all other ready issues | **Parallel** — one worktree per issue |

- Slice status and scope: [`EXECUTION.md`](../../EXECUTION.md)
- Module list: [`docs/architecture/map.md`](../../docs/architecture/map.md)
- Parallel coordination: `.worktrees/issue-<N>/` per branch; one agent owns GitHub ops

## GitHub ops (parallel runs)

When multiple agents run in parallel:

- **One agent** holds the GitHub ops lock — it alone runs `git push`, `gh pr create`,
  `gh pr merge`, `gh pr checks`, and status updates on `main`.
- **All other agents** commit locally only; hand off push/PR/merge to the ops owner.
- **Stagger** remote GitHub commands by at least **30 seconds** between operations.

After each merge, update slice status in `EXECUTION.md` and close or unblock dependent issues.
